parameters.name: IpVersion
parameters.description:
The IP version of the reserved CIDR block. Valid values:

*   **IPv4** (default)
*   **IPv6**

parameters.name: MaxResults
parameters.description: The number of entries to return on each page. Valid values: **1** to **100**. Default value: **10**.

parameters.name: NextToken
parameters.description:
The pagination token that is used in the next request to retrieve a new page of results. Valid values:

*   You do not need to specify this parameter for the first request.
*   You must specify the token that is obtained from the previous query as the value of NextToken.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description:
The region ID of the vSwitch.

You can call the [DescribeRegions](~~36063~~) operation to query the most recent region list.

parameters.name: VSwitchCidrReservationIds
parameters.description: The ID of the reserved CIDR block. You can specify at most 10 IDs.

parameters.name: VSwitchCidrReservationType
parameters.description:
The type of the reserved CIDR block. Set the value to **prefix**.

>  When you allocate CIDR blocks, or enable the service to automatically allocate CIDR blocks to elastic network interfaces (ENIs), the CIDR blocks to allocate must fall into the reserved CIDR block. If the reserved CIDR is exhausted, an error message is returned.

parameters.name: VSwitchId
parameters.description: The ID of the vSwitch for which you want to query reserved CIDR blocks.
